lead_paragraph: AUCKLAND, April 20.--By advices up to this date, it would appear that in consequence of one of the Maori police having struck one of the Ngalipoa tribe, in an at tempt to rescue a prisoner or that tribe from custody, a large body of the natives came in their canoes to demand vengeance. They were completely armed, and well furnished with ammunition. They danced their war dance on the beach.
